                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12471510" author="kartha" created="Thu, 8 Feb 2007 22:42:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any idea by how much the size will increase if we add all these tests to derbyTesting,jar ?  I too was inclined keeping them separate, but on second thoughts, wouldn&apos;t keeping all the Derby testing binaries in derbyTesting.jar avoid any confusion about keeping separate testing jar files ?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12471514" author="djd" created="Thu, 8 Feb 2007 22:53:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe the one jar makes life easier. With two jars the security policy file will have to have an extra section, as it would be good to have these tests running under the security manager at some point. The OETest being already packaged in derbyTesting jar file has worked well for me so far.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also since we don&apos;t provide any ability to download individual jars there&apos;s no benefit there.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12471519" author="fuzzylogic" created="Thu, 8 Feb 2007 23:01:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Big +1 to a single jar. I&apos;d move dynamic generation of the test resources up the list of todos, though, because inclusion of the resource jars will almost double the size of derbyTesting.jar. Considering that we include derbyTesting.jar in all the release distributions, that&apos;s a lot of overhead for nothing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maven projects can and do download the Derby jars individually from the various maven repositories, but I don&apos;t think there would be many maven users who would be interested in including just our system tests in their projects. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12472876" author="mkutty" created="Tue, 13 Feb 2007 21:35:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching the patch for the build.xml files. Also since I got more than one opinion about including the system test classes in the derbyTesting.jar , I withdraw my suggestion to create a new derbysystest.jar. So Now derbyTesting.jar will have the system test classes also.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please review the patch and if everything looks good please commit&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12472929" author="fuzzylogic" created="Wed, 14 Feb 2007 00:05:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Manjula, took a look at the patch. It looks good, one minor problem: I think you forgot to add a &amp;lt;copy&amp;gt; task for the resource jar in the build file for sttest. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I note that after applying this patch, derbyTesting.jar in the jar build is now 11MB. I&apos;d suggest working on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2311&quot; title=&quot; Generate the txt and blobs required for the system tests dynamically &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-2311&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-2311&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; next to bring the size of the derbyTesting.jar file back down.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll hold off on committing this patch for a little while in case anyone objects to the increase in the jar file size.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12476787" author="mkutty" created="Thu, 1 Mar 2007 00:36:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please find the following patches for adding the build.xml to sttest and mailjdbc. Also updated the existing build.xml under testing dir to include both of the tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2309&quot; title=&quot;Add build.xml, so that the code can get compiled using ant with the &amp;#39;all&amp;#39; target.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-2309&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-2309&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;_diff2.txt - for mailjdbc&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2309&quot; title=&quot;Add build.xml, so that the code can get compiled using ant with the &amp;#39;all&amp;#39; target.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-2309&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-2309&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;_diff3.txt - for sttest&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2309&quot; title=&quot;Add build.xml, so that the code can get compiled using ant with the &amp;#39;all&amp;#39; target.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-2309&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-2309&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;_diff4.txt - for testing dir&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12476788" author="mkutty" created="Thu, 1 Mar 2007 00:39:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also attaching the stat file. If everything looks fine please commit&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12476797" author="djd" created="Thu, 1 Mar 2007 01:02:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s much easier for committers if a patch is generated from the top of the source tree (e.g. in the trunk directory), not in individual directories.&lt;br/&gt;
Then they can simply apply the patch from the top of the tree, rather than having to spend time figuring out which directory to cd into.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12477165" author="fuzzylogic" created="Fri, 2 Mar 2007 01:55:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed second set of files with 513583. It would have been better if these three changes had been all in a single patchfile made from the top of the tree.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
